# SynapseHub — local development environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in values you actually need.
# `.env.local` is ignored by git (`.gitignore`); this `.env.example`
# stays committed as the template.
#
# ─── Status as of v0.1.1 ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# SynapseHub itself does NOT consume any custom environment variables.
# The hook server picks a random loopback port at startup, the lock-file
# polling interval is hard-coded in `watcher.rs`, and all runtime
# configuration lives under the OS config directory:
#
#   - Windows: %APPDATA%\synapsehub\
#   - macOS:   ~/Library/Application Support/synapsehub/
#   - Linux:   ~/.config/synapsehub/
#
# This file is kept as a placeholder for future configurability and to
# document the few env vars that influence build / dev tooling today.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Rust logging verbosity, consumed by `env_logger::init()` in
# `src-tauri/src/lib.rs::run`. Levels: error | warn | info | debug | trace.
# Default if unset: warn (env_logger default).
# Useful values:
#   info  — production-like, balanced
#   debug — full hook lifecycle, watcher polls, agent detections
RUST_LOG=info

# Tauri sets TAURI_ENV_DEBUG automatically when you run `npm run tauri dev`.
# vite.config.ts reads it to keep sourcemaps + disable minification in
# development bundles. You normally do NOT set this by hand — uncomment
# only if you build with raw `vite build` outside of Tauri's wrapper.
# TAURI_ENV_DEBUG=1

# ─── Reserved for future use ──────────────────────────────────────────
# When/if SynapseHub starts reading any of the variables below, document
# them here, in `docs/release-process.md`, and in CONTRIBUTING.md.
# Examples (NOT currently consumed by any code path):
#
# SYNAPSEHUB_HOOK_PORT=8765            # Override the random port
# SYNAPSEHUB_POLL_INTERVAL_SECS=2      # Lock-file scan cadence
# SYNAPSEHUB_LOG_FORMAT=text           # text | json
